  "description": "Non-material amendment to planning permission reference:P2019/3481/FUL dated 08/12/2020 for \"Redevelopment of the site at 10 - 18 All Saints Street including the refurbishment and extension of 10-12 All Saints Street (including part roof extension and installation of rooftop plant and enclosure) to provide additional Class B1 business floor space with flexible Class A1/B1/D1 (retail/office/non-residential institutions) floorspace; demolition of 14, 16 and 18 All Saints Street and erection of a part 5 (ground plus 4) and part 6 (ground plus 5) storey building with basement and rooftop plant and enclosures providing Class B1 office floor space and flexible Class A1/A3/B1/D1/D2 (retail/restaurant & cafe/business/non-residential institutions/assembly & leisure) floor space at ground floor; and associated hard and soft landscaping\" . The amendments make the following alterations \r\n\r\nAll Saint's Street South Elevation - Totem height lowered to align with adjacent railing - Door to the Packing House roof terrace added - Update to glazing extents on the Packing House - Colour of brick parapet updated to Packing House - Totem curtain wall fins and panels arrangement developed Eastern Elevation - '- External doors within new curtain walling reduced in size - - Reduction in depth of Aluminium Band Canalside North Elevation - Ground floor timber door replaced with 'Heritage-style' metal door and increased in height to align with adjacent existing windows - Reduction in height of window to L5 extension Western Elevation - Facade material changed from brick to pre-cast concrete to improve facade appearance - Re-alignment of facade fenestration - Nominal increase in height parapets Level 1 & Level 3 to accommodate roof design development - Removal of Bollards - Reduction in Signage Size Shadbolt Square Facades Northern Elevation - Covered courtyard terraces to Level 5 Canal Building incorporated into usable internal space - Balustrade in Courtyard Added - Re-alignment of fenestrat",
